AcceptLanguage.description: List of HTTP headers that specify the natural language, such as English, that the client understands.

DetailIdentifier.description: The ID of the individual detail record. This field is unique within your org.

EventDate.description: The date when the hijacking event was reported. For example, 2020-01-20T19:12:26.965Z. Milliseconds are the most granular setting.

EventIdentifier.description: The unique ID of the event.

EventName.description: The name of the event, which is Credential Stuffing.

LoginType.description: The type of login used to access the session. For the list of possible values, see the LoginType field of LoginHistory in the Object Reference.

LoginUrl.description: The URL of the login page. For example, login.salesforce.com.

MetricIdentifier.description: The ID of the type of metric that was counted.

Name.description: The name of the metric for the data collected.

Score.description: Indicates that a user successfully logged in to Salesforce during an identified credential stuffing attack. The value of this field is always 1.

Summary.description: A summary of the threat that caused this event to be created.

Tenant.description: The ID of the tenant that was targeted in the event.

TenantName.description: The name of the tenant that was targeted in the event.

UserAgent.description: UserAgent used in the HTTP request, post-processed by the server.

Username.description: The origin username in the format of user@company.com at the time the event was created.
